        "author_association": "NONE",
        "body": "> Instead of using symlinks, could you just configure the Gradle build to look at the target of the symlink?\r\n\r\nIf I use absolute paths to target of the symlink, the issue disappears, but this is not ideal as it will involve a decent amount of work on our side. This also seems like something Gradle should handle, though I'm not at all familiar with the Gradle codebase so I have no idea what is actually involved in fixing it. If it's too problematic for Gradle to follow symlinks, let me know and I'll get us to budget some time to workaround on our end. Thanks.\r\n\r\n",
